{"version":"5b3a24064522f051732226670aaa07f3c74d54af34a996eb619c9dd8eb321f84","permit":"No","rappelCountMin":6,"description":"<div class=\"mw-content-ltr mw-parser-output\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><p>A short but action-packed canyon hiding in plain sight near the exit of Eaton Canyon.\n<\/p>\n<meta property=\"mw:PageProp\/toc\" \/>\n<div class=\"mw-heading mw-heading2\"><h2 id=\"Approach\">Approach<\/h2><\/div>\n<p>Take the Altadena Crest Trail and climb the firebreak to the transmission towers. At the towers, turn east and descend the ridge through some brush to the drop-in.\n<\/p>\n<div class=\"mw-heading mw-heading2\"><h2 id=\"Descent\">Descent<\/h2><\/div>\n<p>The canyon starts off with dirt mixed with rock but the rock quality gets better as you descend.\n<\/p><p><b>R1: 70'<\/b> - tree\n<\/p><p><b>R2: 90'<\/b> - tree, multi-step\n<\/p><p><b>R3: 60'<\/b> - tree (banner photo)\n<\/p><p><b>R4: 15'<\/b> - tree\n<\/p><p><b>R5: 25'<\/b> - bush\n<\/p><p><b>R6: 60'<\/b> - bush, multi-step\n<\/p>\n<div class=\"mw-heading mw-heading2\"><h2 id=\"Exit\">Exit<\/h2><\/div>\n<p>The final rappel drops you on the Eaton Canyon Falls Tail between the two dams so the exit is a breeze.\n<\/p>\n<div class=\"mw-heading mw-heading2\"><h2 id=\"Red_tape\">Red tape<\/h2><\/div>\n<div class=\"mw-heading mw-heading2\"><h2 id=\"Beta_sites\">Beta sites<\/h2><\/div>\n<div class=\"mw-heading mw-heading2\"><h2 id=\"Trip_reports_and_media\">Trip reports and media<\/h2><\/div>\n<div class=\"mw-heading mw-heading2\"><h2 id=\"Background\">Background<\/h2><\/div>\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nParsed by mw‐api‐ext.codfw.main‐6779cc57fc‐hfwrl\nCached time: 20240914192015\nCache expiry: 2592000\nReduced expiry: false\nComplications: [show‐toc]\nCPU time usage: 0.005 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.005 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 21\/1000000\nPost‐expand include size: 0\/2097152 bytes\nTemplate argument size: 0\/2097152 bytes\nHighest expansion depth: 2\/100\nExpensive parser function count: 0\/